= Build Simple bgeo Clip =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Builds a USD value clip set from a bgeo sequence file."""

== Overview ==

Build Simple bgeo Clip creates a USD stage that references a bgeo geometry sequence as a USD value clip. This allows Houdini geometry caches to be consumed natively in a USD pipeline without full conversion.

The bgeo files must have a sample frame detail attribute set by a `usdconfigure` SOP.

Output 1 is the clip stage. Output 2 is a template stage.

When writing to disk, a manifest sidecar file (`<output>.manifest.usd`) is generated next to the output USD. The output's clip metadata references it with a relative path, so the manifest must always travel alongside the output file.

TIP:
    Use __Use Relative Paths__ when the output USD file and bgeo sequence share a common root directory to keep the setup portable.

@parameters

File:
    #id: filepath
    Path to the bgeo sequence. Supports `$F` frame substitution.

Reload Files:
    #id: reload
    Forces a reload of the bgeo sequence from disk.

Template Frame:
    #id: template_frame
    Frame number used as the clip template (topology reference). Default: `1`.

Clip:
    #id: clip
    Name of the USD clip set. Default: `default`.

Files Frame Start/End:
    #id: frame_range
    Frame range of the source bgeo sequence on disk.

Scene Frame Start/End:
    #id: scene_range
    Frame range the clip maps to in the USD scene.

Loop:
    #id: loop
    When enabled, the clip loops back to the start after the last frame.

Primitive:
    #id: primpath
    Target USD primitive path that will reference the clip. Must match the prim path the bgeo imports to (determined by the `usdconfigure` SOP). Default: `/Geometry`.

Output File:
    #id: lopoutput
    File path to write the output USD clip file. A `.manifest.usd` sidecar is written next to it.

Save to Disk:
    #id: execute
    Writes the output USD clip file and generates the manifest sidecar.

Use Relative Paths:
    #id: enableoutputprocessor_simplerelativepaths
    Writes relative asset paths in the output USD file.
